Class PubSub

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    org.jivesoftware.smack.packet.Element, org.jivesoftware.smack.packet.Packet, org.jivesoftware.smack.packet.TopLevelStreamElement

    public class PubSub
extends org.jivesoftware.smack.packet.IQ
    The standard PubSub extension of an IQ packet. This is the topmost element of all pubsub requests and replies as defined in the Publish-Subscribe specification.

        protected org.jivesoftware.smack.packet.IQ.IQChildElementXmlStringBuilder getIQChildElementBuilder(org.jivesoftware.smack.packet.IQ.IQChildElementXmlStringBuilder xml)
        Returns the XML representation of a pubsub element according the specification. The XML representation will be inside of an iq stanza(/packet) like in the following example: 
         <iq type='set' id="MlIpV-4" to="pubsub.gato.home" from="gato3@gato.home/Smack">
     <pubsub xmlns="http://jabber.org/protocol/pubsub">
                      :

                      :
     </pubsub>
 </iq>
